race.comment: THE LAST CRUSADE (9) proved too strong for the 65 graders this track and distance and boasts five wins here. Led them up and draws the paint today. No surprise to see him deliver again. ARDEN GREEN (5) got the prize two runs ago at Charleville but couldn't follow that up last time when he found one much too good there over a mile. Better suited today and has an inside gate and handy 2kg claim. A bounce isn't out of the question. BLAZERRO (3) has switched yards since scoring by 2L at Home Hill over 1830m just 9 days ago. Has to come back to a sprint but must be pleasing and keep onside. BENEVENTO (6) had excuses last time, but his form prior is solid for this. He also has claims.
